The paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), hence cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions language modeling, which is a subfield of NLP and ML, and neural networks for sequence modeling, which is relevant to neural networks and DL, hence cs.NE is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on translation tasks, which is a common application of computer vision (CV) and NLP, hence cs.CV is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
